<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id780c9ccb-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460zzz–5"><num value="460zzz–5">§ 460zzz–5.</num><heading> Management plan</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id780c9ccc-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460zzz–5/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 3 years after <date date="2009-03-30">March 30, 2009</date>, the Secretary shall develop a comprehensive management plan for the long-term protection and management of the Conservation Area.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id780c9ccd-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460zzz–5/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Purposes</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The management plan shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id780c9cce-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460zzz–5/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> describe the appropriate uses and management of the Conservation Area;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id780c9ccf-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460zzz–5/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> be developed with extensive public input;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id780c9cd0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460zzz–5/b/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> take into consideration any information developed in studies of the land within the Conservation Area; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id780c9cd1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460zzz–5/b/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> include a comprehensive travel management plan.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id780c9cd2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/11/tII/s2406">Pub. L. 111–11, title II, § 2406</ref>, <date date="2009-03-30">Mar. 30, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/1107">123 Stat. 1107</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
